number: APT41
overview: APT41, aka Volt-typhoon, Vanguard Panda, BRONZE SILHOUETTE, Dev-0391, UNC3236, Voltzite, and Insidious Taurus, is a PRC state-sponsored cyber group accused of seeking to pre-position themselves on IT networks for disruptive or destructive cyberattacks against the United States. The Intelligence Community released an advisory in February 07, 2024 highlighting their threats (https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/cybersecurity-advisories/aa24-038a).
targetSectors: U.S. Critical Infrastructure
previousAttacks: Critical Infrastructure within continental and non-continental US and its territories. Attacks not consistent with common intelligence-gathering techniques, highlighting motivations of pre-positioning.
